Keeps it bowling fuller, Pant flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Iyer defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one as Iyer drives it firmly back towards the bowler who gets a hand on it before the ball goes on to hit the stumps at the bowler's end.
This one lands on off, Iyer taps it to the man at covers.
Goes fuller and on off, Iyer knocks it to long on for a single.
Fuller and slower, down leg. Pant looks to defend it but gets a rap on his pads. A stifled appeal turned down.
Bowls it outside off, Pant steers it to the man at covers. Ends with a dot.
Fuller and slower on middle, Iyer defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller again, Iyer lunges and blocks it away.
Bowls it on off, Iyer eases it to mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter and slower, Iyer works it to mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Tossed up on leg stump, Rishabh Pant dances down the track and whips it over the leaping man at wide mid on for a boundary.! The 100-run stand is up between this duo now.
SIX! Fuller and on off, Pant shimmies down the wicket and heaves it over the long on fence for a maximum! 200 up for India now!
Fuller and on off, Iyer defends it to covers.
SIX! Bowls it fuller and on off, Iyer dances down the track and lofts it over wide long on for a maximum!
Fuller and on off, Iyer lunges and blocks it away.
Outside off, this is defended out solidly.
Slightly shorter and on off, Iyer flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
SIX! What a shot. Pant you beauty! Fuller and on off, Pant moves forward and lofts it with one hand over long on for a maximum! That has travelled beyond a 100 meters, unreal!
Starts off with a shortish ball around leg stump, Iyer works it off his hips toward backward square leg.
Banged in short and over middle, Shreyas Iyer with a cracking pull shot but finds the man at square leg.

That will be FIFTY for Shreyas Iyer, his 2nd one against Bangladesh. Shorter, bowled from around the stumps and around leg stump. Iyer pulls it down to fine leg for a single. India now trail by just 11 runs.
A good bumper, over middle and Rishabh Pant just lets it through to the keeper.
Another short ball down the leg side, Pant ducks under it with ease.
Shorter in length and on the body, Pant plays a controlled pull shot through backward square leg and picks up a single.
Shakib Al Hasan brings himself back into the attack and tosses it up full and outside off. Rishabh Pant looks to fetch and sweep but miscues it through mid-wicket. Pant will get the single though.
Well bowled! Slows it up a touch and drifts it onto middle, the ball turns away after pitching but Iyer is able to watchfully keep it out.
Tossed up around middle, Shreyas Iyer blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery, on a length and outside off, Iyer eases it to short extra cover.
SIX! Picks up the length early and dispatches it. This is dragged down by Shakib on off stump, Shreyas Iyer rocks back and pulls it all the way over the cow corner fence for a maximum.
A tad shorter and on leg stump, this is worked away down to wide long on for a single.
Khaled comes from around the wicket and keeps bowling it short and at the body. Iyer shuffles a bit and tucks it to square leg.
Banged in short and over middle and leg, this is pulled away straight to mid-wicket.
Through the fielder! Another short ball around leg stump, Shreyas Iyer gets on top of the bounce and pulls it firmly toward square leg where Mominul Haque misfields and allows the single to be taken.
Back to over the wicket now and serves a length ball on leg stump. Rishabh Pant defends it out.
An attempted bumper around middle and off, Pant just bends his back a bit and leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Back of a length, over middle and Pant just defends it down toward silly point. A dot to end and that will be Tea on Day 2!
On a hard length and angling into the off pole, Shreyas Iyer gets behind the line of the ball to make the block.
Pushed away and India are now in the lead by 1 run! Pitched up around off, Iyer presses forward and strokes it through the cover region for a couple of runs.
Fullish length outside off, driven straight to the man at extra cover.
Staying low! Banged in on a hard length and around off, Iyer looks to pull but the ball stays low and goes under the willow, dying on its way to the keeper.
Back of a length and close to the off pole, Iyer allows the ball to come to him before punching it away to deep point for a run.
A bit of an uneven bounce here. On a good length, bowled from around the stumps and on off stump, Pant looks to block off the front foot but gets a bit taken aback by the extra bounce.
Khaled digs it in short first up and at the body, there to be hit but Iyer mistimes it badly toward square leg.
Another one begging to be hit but Shreyas Iyer fails to put it away. This is dragged down over middle, sitting up nicely for the batter but it is hit straight to square leg.
A good bumper now, over middle and Shreyas Iyer just lets it through to the keeper.
Keeps on banging it in short and on the body, Iyer pulls it down to deep backward square leg for a single.
Comes from around the wicket now and bangs it in halfway down the track, flying over Pant's head. The short ball tactic isn't coming off for Khaled Ahmed.
FOUR! Short again and around off, sits up nicely for the batter. Rishabh Pant rocks back and muscles it in front of mid-wicket for a boundary. He moves into the 90s now.
Length ball, a touch fuller and angling into off stump, Iyer watchfully keeps it out.
FOUR! A rank half-volley outside off, Shreyas Iyer stands tall and thumps it uppishly through extra cover for a boundary. Bangladesh currently seem to have no answer to this hitting.
Switches to around the wicket and bowls a bumper over leg stump, Iyer is able to get inside the line and play a controlled pull shot down to fine leg for one.
Slower one, pitched up on middle and leg, Pant flicks it through mid-wicket and turns the strike over.
Pitched up around middle, this is driven firmly but straight to mid on.
Shortish length around leg stump, Iyer swivels and tucks it down to deep backward square leg for another easy single.
Banged in short and well down the leg side, Iyer doesn't play at it.

FOUR! Much better from Khaled but still the ball ends up in the ropes. Goes full and angles it just across off, Shreyas Iyer is late on the drive but gets it through the vacant mid off region. The ball trickles away into the fence and the 150-run stand is up between these two.
Goes back to bowling it short and around leg stump, Iyer fails to get it away.
A sharp bouncer now, on the money. This is bowled around leg stump and angling across the helmet of the batter. Iyer sways away from the line of the ball.
Banged in halfway down the track and down leg as well. Shreyas Iyer leaves it alone and Khaled Ahmed has a bit of a chat with him. Iyer grins and frustrates the bowler further.
This is short and outside off, Iyer pulls it down to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Floated up, full and around middle, this is flicked away straight to square leg.

Close but not close enough for Bangladesh! This is flatter around off, keeping a tad low. Shreyas Iyer punches it off the back foot toward extra cover where the fielder makes half a stop. The batters look for the quick single but the fielder from mid off is quick to latch onto it. Pant is sent back and the bowler does whip off the bails. The replays show that Pant dived in well and made his ground.
Beaten! Tossed up on a shorter length and around off, Iyer looks to play it off the back foot but is well beaten.
Tossed up on middle, this is eased away through covers for one.
Shorter and around off, played off the back foot onto the off side for one more.
FOUR! Sweetly timed! A tad shorter and around middle, Shreyas Iyer waits for it and pushes it back past the bowler for a boundary.
Shakib starts off with a flighted delivery outside off, Pant watches it closely and leaves it alone.
Tossed up, on a nagging length and around off, Pant looks to block but is beaten past the outside edge.
On the pads, Pant tucks it toward backward square leg.
Nicely flighted, fuller and wide of the off stump. Rishabh Pant looks to get a big stride across and block but is beaten once again.
Keeps it around off, Pant is able to push it away onto the off side of a single.
Nicely flighted, on middle and leg, Iyer blocks it out.
Floated, full and outside off, left alone by Pant.
Tosses it up now, full and around middle, Pant plays it with soft hands toward backward point.
Drifted onto middle and leg, Pant defends it out.
Nicely drifted into the pads this time, Pant blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Rishabh Pant departs in the nervous 90s for the sixth time in his Test career and the crowd is absolutely elated. Mehidy Hasan goes a bit wider of the crease and floats it up on a nagging length around the off pole. The ball does turn away a bit but Pant goes on the back foot instead of coming forward and looks to have a dab at it. The ball deflects off the outside edge and goes into Nurul Hasan's gloves. Pant departs after yet another game-changing knock and India now lead by 26 runs.
Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: A wicket-maiden! This is fired in on off stump, Axar Patel pushes it out on the off side.
This is slower and shorter around middle, Shreyas Iyer works it off the back foot through mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up full and on middle, flicked away toward mid-wicket.
Floated full and outside off, Axar Patel drives it straight toward extra cover.

Half an appeal from the fielders but the umpire isn't interested. This is angling into the pads, Axar goes deep in his crease and nudges it in front of short leg who throws the ball onto the stumps and appeals for a run out.
Length ball on the pads, flicked away towards square leg.
Quicker one, outside off and left alone for the keeper to collect.
Very full and on off stump, Shreyas Iyer keeps it out on the leg side.
Flighted delivery, full and outside off, Iyer leans on and eases it through cover-point for one.
This is pushed through fuller and around middle, Axar Patel pushes at it with hard hands and past the man at silly point.
EDGED AND FOUR! This is flatter and around off stump, Axar Patel rocks back to cut but gets a thick outside edge that runs away into the third man fence.
Flighted and on the pads, Axar nudges it towards leg gully.
Floated up on middle, Axar Patel pushes it toward mid on.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on leg, Shreyas Iyer gets on his knees and sweeps it through backward square leg for a boundary!
Fuller again, on off. Shreyas Iyer moves forward and knocks it to extra covers for one.

OUT! TAKEN! Axar goes for the big one as he gets the height and not the distance. This is fuller and on off, Axar Patel lofts it over mid off. The ball goes in the air near the ropes and Najmul Hossain Shanto takes a good catch over his head and just stops before the ropes. They check the replay if he has touched the fence, and it shows he hasn't. The big screen shows OUT and Axar Patel makes his way back into the hut.
Howout: c Najmul Hossain Shanto b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin taps it to the man at mid on.
Bowls it on off, Ravichandran Ashwin defends it to the man at silly point.
This one lands down middle and leg, Ravichandran Ashwin lunges and defends it away.
Fuller and on off, Iyer defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, Iyer eases it to the man at mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Iyer punches it to covers for one.
FOUR! Lovely shot. Fuller and on off, Ashwin flicks it using his wrists through mid-wicket for a boundary!
This one lands on off, Ashwin defends it to silly point.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards the man at point.
Bowls it on off, Iyer drives it to covers for a single.
Fuller and on off, Iyer eases it to covers and scampers through for a single. There was a midfield from the fielder. If he had been quick to grab the ball this would have been close!
Fuller and on off, Iyer defends it solidly off the front foot.

OUT! PLUMB! Fuller and on off with a hint of turn, Shreyas Iyer looks to sweep it away but misses and the ball hits his thigh. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Shreyas Iyer decides to go upstairs. Fair delivery and Ultra Edge shows a flat line. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Shreyas Iyer has to walk out. He departs for 87!
Howout: lbw b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Jaydev Unadkat defends it to short covers.
Bowls it outside off, Jaydev Unadkat taps it to covers again.
Short and wide, Ashwin cuts it away to the diving point fielder.
Another fuller ball, Ashwin eases it to mid off.
Bowls it on off, Ashwin defends it to mid off again.
This one lands on middle, Ashwin taps it to the man at mid on.
Fuller and on off, Ashwin drives it to deep covers for one.
Bowls it on middle with some turn, Unadkat guides it to backward point for a single.
Bowls it outside leg, Unadkat leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Unadkat defends it solidly.
Outside off this time, Unadkat let's it through towards the keeper.
Fuller one again, Unadkat lunges and blocks it away.
Bowls it fuller and keeps a tad low, Unadkat defends it again.
FOUR! Nice shot. Fuller and on middle, Unadkat gets on his knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary!
Bowls it on off, this is defended out solidly.
Another fuller one, Ashwin lunges and defends it to mid off.
Tossed up on middle, Ashwin taps it to the man at covers.
Another one outside off, Ashwin knocks it to covers for a single.
Quicker one outside off, Unadkat looks to defend it but misses.
Tosses it up on off, Unadkat lunges and blocks it away.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Ashwin defends it with soft hands.
Quicker one on leg, Ashwin looks to play at it but gets his pads as the ball lobs to the man at short leg who drops it.
Short and wide, Ashwin cuts it away to the diving point fielder.

Nicely tossed up by Shakib Al Hasan as he sees Ravichandran Ashwin coming down the track and this one is angled into middle stump. Ashwin looks to block but fails to get his front leg out of the way and there is a huge shout by the Bangladeshi players for lbw. It is turned down and Shakib reviews it immediately. Nothing on UltraEdge and everything seems fine on Ball Tracking as well but the impact is more than 3 meters in front of the stumps and hence it cannot be given out. Ashwin survives!

FOUR! Fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin moves forward and lofts it over mid on for a boundary! He brings up 3000 runs in Test cricket and becomes the second-fastest player to 400 wickets and 3000 runs behind Sir Richard Hadlee.
Fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin lunges and defends it away.
Goes fuller and on off, Jaydev Unadkat lunges and blocks it away.
Fuller one with some turn, Jaydev Unadkat looks to block it but miscues it to mid-wicket. They cross.
Fuller length around off, Ashwin drives it to the diving cover fielder.
Bowls it fuller again, Ravichandran Ashwin taps it to extra covers. Dot.
Fuller on the stumps as Ashwin defends it back to the bowler.

Fuller and on the middle with a sharp turn away from the batter, Ravichandran Ashwin looks to defend it but misses. Taijul Islam thinks that there was a slight edge and Shakib Al Hasan decides to go upstairs. Replay shows that there was no bat involved and the onfield decision stands.
Full on the stumps. Unadkat defends it to short covers.
Bowls it fuller again, Jaydev Unadkat moves forward to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his pads. Dot.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards mid off.
Slightly shorter one, Jaydev Unadkat cuts it but finds the fielder at point.
Fuller one and on off, Jaydev Unadkat lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
This was similar to the last delivery, Jaydev Unadkat again blocks it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, Ravichandran Ashwin eases it to the man at mid on.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin eases it to short covers.
This one lands on off, Ravichandran Ashwin knocks it to long off for one.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Jaydev Unadkat defends it to short covers.
This one lands on off turning it away from the right-hander, Jaydev Unadkat punches it to point for a brace.
Fuller and quicker too, Jaydev Unadkat blocks it back towards the bowler.

OUT! LBW! The skipper has done the job for his team and India lose their eighth. This is flatter and angled into middle and leg. Ashwin looks to come forward and block but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a loud appeal and Shakib Al Hasan strikes straightaway with the new ball as Ravichandran Ashwin has been deemed lbw. Ashwin does review it though. UltraEdge is checked first and there's no spike on it. Ball Tracking shows that the ball is clipping leg stump and Ashwin has to walk back. That wicket was also Shakib's 650th wicket in all of international cricket!
Howout: lbw b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary: Tossed up around off, Umesh Yadav blocks it out.

FOUR! Streaky but India won't mind. Quicker one, angled into middle, Umesh Yadav looks to block but there's a big gap between bat and pad. The ball takes the inside edge and goes past the leg stump and into the fine leg fence.
Tossed up, full and on leg stump, Yadav heaves it down to long on for a single.
Drops it a bit short and on off, Jaydev Unadkat punches it toward cover for a run.
Flighted delivery, on off stump, Umesh Yadav solidly keeps it out off the front foot.
Taskin Ahmed comes back in to share the new ball with his skipper. This is full and outside off, just seaming away a touch. Jaydev Unadkat leaves it alone.
Fuller and well outside off again, Unadkat isn't going to play at that one.
Just not finding his rhythm yet Taskin. This is a length ball pushed well outside the off stump and edging on being called a wide. Nurul Hasan though makes a good diving stop to his right.
FOUR! Banged in short and over middle, Jaydev Unadkat gets on top of the bounce and pulls it away into the square leg fence for a boundary.
On a good length around off, this is tapped away toward point.
Back of a length and outside off, left alone for the keeper to collect.
Tossed up, around off and this is defended off the front foot.
Nicely flighted, on a nagging length and around middle, just turning away a touch. Yadav manages to keep it out.
FOUR! Slapped away! Short and outside off, Umesh Yadav rocks back and cuts it past point for a boundary. The 300 is now up for India.
Tosses it up now, inviting the bog shot, Yadav mistimes the heave toward extra cover.
This is sliding in from off stump, Yadav pushes it toward mid on.
Floated up full and at the stumps, Umesh Yadav knocks it down to long on for a single.
FOUR! Taijul Islam comes into the attack and starts off with a quicker one down leg. Umesh Yadav just tickles it into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Flighted delivery, on off stump and blocked off the front foot by Yadav.

OUT! CAUGHT! Umesh Yadav's quickfire inning comes to an end and India now lead by 78 runs. Taijul Islam tosses this one up on a length and outside the off stump. The ball is turning away and Yadav looks for the big heave across the line. The ball takes the toe end of the bat and goes toward the first slip where Litton Das takes a comfortable catch around his face. Taijul is now one wicket away from a five-fer.
Howout: c Litton Das b Taijul Islam

Commentary: Slows it up a touch and bowls it around off, Mohammed Siraj leans forward to block.
Flatter one on middle, Siraj is able to block it out.
This is drifted down the leg side, Siraj waits for it and just nudges it fine past the diving fielder at leg slip for a couple of runs.
Flighted delivery around off, Unadkat keeps it out.
Pulls back the length and bowls it around middle, Jaydev Unadkat works it leg side for a single.
Nicely drifted onto the leg stump, Siraj prods and blocks it out.
Looped up, full and on middle, Mohammed Siraj lunges forward and keeps it out.
Flighted, around middle, Siraj makes yet another good block.
Leg bye! Shorter and down leg, Siraj looks to tuck it away but the ball deflects off the pads and goes towards fine leg. They get a leg bye.
Flighted delivery on off, dipping on the batter and Siraj blocks it out.
Holds it back a touch and drifts it onto middle and leg, Siraj makes another block off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle, Mohammed Siraj advances and whips it helicopter-style towards mid-wicket.
Beaten! Nicely flighted around off and turning away, Siraj looks to defend but the ball goes past the outside edge.
This is tossed up on middle and leg, Mohammed Siraj dances down the track and looks for the heave leg side but completely miscues it down to long off for a single.
Quicker one, around middle, this one stays low and skids on as well. Jaydev Unadkat manages to keep it out on the off side.
Floats this one up, full and on leg stump, Mohammed Siraj keeps it out off the front foot.
FOUR! Tossed up on a length and around off, Siraj plays the sweep against the turn and hits it uppishly to the left of the man at square leg for a boundary.

OUT! STUMPED! That's it Shakib Al Hasan picks up his fourth wicket and India are bowled out late on Day 2. Mohammed Siraj pre-meditates and shimmies down the track. Shakib holds it back and pushes it wider of the off pole. Siraj throws the kitchen sink at it but gets beaten in the flight and the ball keeps a bit low as well. Nurul Hasan whips off the bails and Siraj seems very disappointed. India finish with 314 runs on the board and lead by 87 runs.
Howout: st Nurul Hasan b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary: On a length in the channel outside off, shaping it away. Najmul Hossain Shanto leaves it alone.
This one lands outside leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to flick it but misses.
Good length shaping it away, Najmul Hossain Shanto leaves it through towards the keeper.
On a length with some extra bounce, Najmul Hossain Shanto fends it to square leg.
Bowls it outside leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to flick it but misses.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto fends it to mid off. Umesh Yadav starts with a maiden!
Fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan defends it solidly.
Another fuller one, on off. Zakir Hasan lunges and blocks it away.
Bowls it on off again, Zakir Hasan blocks it to short covers.
This one lands outside off, Zakir Hasan looks to cut it but misses.
Bowls it on off again, Zakir Hasan blocks it to silly point.
Quicker one down leg, Zakir Hasan shuffles across to flick it but misses and gets a rap on his pads. A maiden from Ravichandran Ashwin!

FOUR! Bowls it on a length and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races away the third man fence. Lucky boundary! Najmul Hossain Shanto is off the mark.
Fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it to the leg side.
Good length shaping it away, Najmul Hossain Shanto lets it through towards the keeper.
On a length shaping it in, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it solidly.
Good length and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it to short covers.
Good length with some extra bounce, outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto shoulders arms at it.
Slightly shorter and on off, Zakir Hasan flicks it to mid-wicket for one. Najmul Hossain Shanto wanted a second run but Zakir Hasan sends him back.
Fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it to covers.
Bowls it on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto knocks it to the man at mid on.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto lunges and blocks it away.
Quicker and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to slog it but gets a bottom edge as the ball rolls towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto drills it to mid on for one.
Fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto taps it to mid on.
Good length and on middle and leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto knocks it to mid on.
On a length and just outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it back towards the bowler.
Touch fuller, on middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto eases it to the man at point.
Bowls it fuller and outside leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to flick it but misses.
On a length and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it to silly point. A maiden from Jaydev Unadkat!
Flatter and on middle and leg, Zakir Hasan covers his line and blocks it away.
Fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Tosses it up on off, Zakir Hasan blocks this one towards the man at mid off.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Zakir Hasan punches it to covers for a single.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it solidly.
Bowls it outside off with a hint of turn, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to block it but misses. That will be STUMPS for Day 2.
Starts with a length ball shaping it away, Hasan shoulders arms at it.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and outside off, Hasan caresses it through extra covers for a boundary!
Bowls it on off, Hasan opens the face of the bat and guides it to the man at point.
On a length and on leg with some extra bounce, Hasan fends it to square leg.
Good length and on leg, Hasan flicks it to square leg for a single.
Slightly shorter and outside off shaping it away, Najmul Hossain Shanto leaves it through towards the keeper. Ends with a dot.
Fuller and angling into the pads, Zakir tucks it away for a single to the leg side.
Bowls it on off, this is defended towards covers.
Fuller and on off, Shanto blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller one and on off, Shanto lunges and defends it solidly.

Tosses it up on middle and leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to defend it but misses as the ball hits his elbow. A loud appeal but the finger stays down. Ravichandran Ashwin opts for a review. Ball Tracking shows that it was above the stumps and the decision stays NOT OUT!

OUT! LBW! Bowls it fuller and on off turning it in, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to block it but gets a rap on his pads. A loud appeal and the finger goes up this time. Najmul Hossain Shanto opts for a review. Fair delivery and Ultra Edge shows a flat line. Ball Tracking shows three reds and the onfield decision stands. Najmul Hossain Shanto departs and India have an early breakthrough.
Howout: lbw b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: On a length and outside off, Hasan leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Bowls it fuller this time, Hasan defends it to short covers.

Fuller one shaping it away, Hasan looks like block it but misses and gets a rap on his pads. A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Siraj opts to review it at the very end. Ball Tracking shows that it was pitching outside leg and the onfield decision stands NOT OUT!
This one lands outside off shaping it away, Hasan let's it go.
Good length and on middle, Hasan flicks it to square leg for a single.
Good length and outside off, Haque shoulders arms at it.
Fuller and angling it in, Hasan defends it solidly.
Bowls it fuller again, Hasan lunges and blocks it out.
Keeps it bowling fuller as Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
This one lands on off, Hasan defends it to covers.
Bowls it on middle, Hasan blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Goes fuller and outside off, Hasan pushes it to mid off for one.
Fuller one and on off, Hasan taps it to the man at covers.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Hasan looks to slap it but misses.
FOUR! Fine shot. On a length and outside off, Hasan opens the face of the bat and guides it through backward point for a boundary!
On a length with some extra bounce, Hasan fends it to point.
Fuller one and just outside off, Hasan flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Bowls it fuller and on middle and leg, Haque defends it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up giving it some air, Hasan knocks it to mid off for one.
Fuller and on off, Haque defends it to the man at mid off.
Outside off this time, Haque goes for a wild swing towards deep point for one. That could have gone anywhere.
Fuller and on off as Hasan defends it to mid on.
Another fuller one as Hasan blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Keeps bowling it fuller, Hasan lunges and blocks it away.
On a length and on middle, Haque defends it back towards the bowler.
Another length ball shaping it in, Haque defends it to short covers.
Fuller and on off, Haque eases it to mid on. Dot.
FOUR! Good shot. Fuller and on middle and leg, Haque whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary!

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Mominul Haque walks out. Mohammed Siraj strikes and India have their second of the morning. On a length and just outside off, it shapes it away a bit. Mominul Haque looks to block it but gets beaten all ends up. Gets a slight outside edge and Rishabh Pant behind the sticks makes no mistake.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: On a length with some extra bounce, Shakib Al Hasan leaves it alone.
Tossed up on off, Hasan defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside off turning it away, Hasan looks to play at it but misses.
Bowls it on off, Hasan blocks it to short covers.
Slightly shorter one as this is defended back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside off, Hasan reads it well and leaves it alone.
Outside off again with some turn, Hasan leaves it alone.
Good length angling it in, Shakib taps it to covers for a single.
Slightly shorter and outside off as this shapes away sharply, Zakir Hasan looks to block it but misses.
On a length and on off, Zakir Hasan taps it to the man at short covers.
Bowls it outside off, Zakir Hasan looks to slap it but misses. This is good bowling from Mohammed Siraj!
On a length and on off, Zakir Hasan taps it to short covers. Dot again.
Good length angling it into the batter, Zakir Hasan fends it to point. Ends with a dot.
Bowls it on leg, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it to deep backward square leg for a brace.
Another one on leg, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it to square leg for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Zakir Hasan tucks it to mid-wicket for one more.
Fuller one turning it away, Shakib Al Hasan defends it to silly point.
Another fuller one, Shakib Al Hasan knocks it to covers for one.
Fuller and outside off, Zakir Hasan reads it well and lets it go.
On a length angling it in, Shakib taps it back towards the bowler.
On a length and just outside off shaping it away, Shakib looks to drive it but misses.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Shakib plays a classic cover drive through covers for a boundary!
Fuller and outside off, this one kept a tad low. Shakib looks to drive it but misses.
A wayward bouncer on leg, Shakib ducks underneath it. Wided.
Fuller and on off, Shakib knocks it straight to the man at mid off.
Shorter and on middle and leg, Shakib ducks underneath it.
Fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan flicks it to short mid-wicket and calls for one. The fielder is quick to get it and has a shy but misses. A direct hit would have been close!
On off, this is defended out solidly.
Another one on off as Zakir Hasan pushes it to covers.
Fuller one drifting on the off stump, this is pushed forward to the covers.
Fuller and just outside off, Zakir Hasan looks to slog it but misses. Close!
Bowls it fuller and on off, Shakib defends it to mid on.
On a length and on leg, Shakib defends it solidly.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards the man at covers.
On a length and on middle and leg, Shakib flicks it to square leg for a single.
Good length with some extra bounce, Zakir fends it to mid on.
Bowls it outside off, Zakir taps it to the man at covers.
Tossed up on off, Shakib eases it to covers.
Bowls it on off, Shakib guides it to point and scampers through for a single.
Fuller and on off, Zakir lunges and blocks it away.
Keeps bowling it fuller, Zakir guides it to backward point for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Shakib hangs back and blocks it out.
Another fuller delivery as Shakib defends this one to short covers.
On a length and on off, Zakir Hasan taps it to short covers. Dot.
Fuller one outside off shaping it in, Zakir Hasan leaves it alone.
Bowls it outside off again, Zakir Hasan leaves the harmless delivery.
On a length with some extra bounce, Zakir Hasan fends it to covers.
Good length and outside off, slower too. Zakir Hasan lets it go.
FOUR! Great timing. Fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan drives it into the gap through covers for a boundary!
Tossed up from around the stumps and on middle, Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out.
This is drifted onto middle and leg, Shakib looks to drive at it but gets an inside edge.
A juicy full toss now around off, Shakib Al Hasan drives it toward extra cover where the fielder fumbles and allows a single.
This is angled into the pads, Zakir looks to turn it leg side but gets a leading edge that lands well short of the bowler.
Floated up around middle, Zakir Hasan gets an outside edge while looking to drive at it.
Tossed up full and around off, Zakir Hasan drives it down to long off and picks up a single.
Good length, bowled from around off and angled into off stump, Zakir defends it from inside his crease.
Fullish length outside off, this is tapped away past the point fielder for a single.
A bumper now, over leg stump and angling further down leg, Shakib ducks under it well.
Around the top of off, Shakib hangs back and nudges it out on the leg side.
Goes a bit wider of the crease and angles in a length ball into off stump, Shakib Al Hasan plays it with soft hands in front of mid-wicket.
Loose shot but Shakib gets away with it. Fullish length, well outside off and Shakib looks for the expansive drive. The ball goes past the outside edge through to the keeper.
Nicely drifted onto middle and leg, Zakir Hasan presses forward and tickles it 'round the corner for a single. The 50 is up for Bangladesh.
Flighted delivery, around middle, solidly kept out on the off side.
Nicely tossed up outside off, inviting the drive and Shakib Al Hasan does drive but straight to the man at cover.
Pulls the length back and turns it away from off stump, Shakib Al Hasan gets caught in two minds but does manage to just keep it out.
LEG BYE! This is down the leg side, Shakib looks to flick but gets it off the pads toward fine leg and they collect a leg bye.
Loopy delivery, on middle, Zakir Hasan frees his arms and strokes it toward cover.
Starts off with a length ball, angling in from around off, Shakib hangs back and watchfully keeps it out.

Uppish but safe! On a hard length and around off, Shakib Al Hasan tries to get on the front foot but the ball bounces a bit extra and the ball goes off the shoulder of the bat but wide of the man at gully.
Around the top of off, Shakib solidly defends it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is a soft dismissal and the bowling change has worked wonders for India. This is served on a length and around off, angling in. Shakib Al Hasan presses forward and pushes at the ball with hard hands. The ball bounces a bit extra again and comes off the sticker of the bat. The ball goes straight toward short cover where Shubman Gill takes a simple catch in front of him. Unadkat gets the breakthrough and Shakib will be highly disappointed with that stroke.
Howout: c Shubman Gill b Jaydev Unadkat

Commentary: Pitches this one up in that channel around off, Mushfiqur Rahim leaves it alone.
A wicket-maiden! Comes from around the wicket now and tries to angle one in at the stumps. Mushfiqur Rahim watches it well and keeps it out on the off side. Bangladesh still trail by 36 runs.
Flighted delivery on middle and Zakir Hasan strides forward to defend.
Tossed up from around the wicket and on middle again, Zakir stays solid in defense.
Play and a miss! Nicely tossed up, full and outside off, turning away as well. Zakir Hasan looks for the booming cover drive but is beaten all ends up.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tossed up around off again, this time Zakir Hasan holds his shape and just lofts it inside-out over covers for a boundary.
A tad shorter and down leg, Zakir awkwardly fends it to the right of the keeper.
Flighted, on a nagging length and around off. The ball bounces a bit extra but Zakir does well to nudge it out toward point.
Back of a length on off stump and angling across, Mushfiqur Rahim gets behind the line to make the block.
Good length over off stump, Rahim defends it back on the deck.
Good length around off, Mushfiqur Rahim presses forward and bunts it in front of covers for a quick single to get off the mark.
Nicely bowled. A touch fuller and closer to the off stump, just straightening a bit. Zakir Hasan plays inside the line as the ball stays a bit low as well.
Good length, angled into middle and leg, Zakir Hasan gets an inside edge through square leg and picks up a single.
Full and straight, clipped away past square leg for one more.
Quicker one, on a nagging length and around off, Mushfiqur Rahim goes on the back foot to ease it through cover-point for a single.
Nicely tossed up, full and on off stump, Zakir Hasan drives it firmly toward extra cover.
Tosses it up now outside off, Zakir Hasan lofts it over extra cover and picks up a single in the deep.
On a length and turning into the pads, Rahim tucks it past short leg for a run.
Shorter and turning away from around off, Zakir taps it toward gully.
Flighted delivery, on the fifth stump line and turning away sharply. Zakir Hasan plays well inside the line of the ball.

A bit of hesitation from the batters but no harm is done. This is full and straight, Mushfiqur Rahim clips it past square leg and looks for two right away. Mohammed Siraj in the deep picks it up and throws it at the keeper's end but it was Zakir Hasan who was struggling a bit on the other end.
Fullish length around off, pushed away toward cover.
Around the top of off, Mushfiqur Rahim watchfully keeps it out.
Length again, angling in from around middle, Mushfiqur Rahim tucks it away toward square leg for a single.
Bangs it in a bit short and angling into the body, Zakir Hasan hops and manages to keep it out.
Pitches it up now on off stump, Zakir Hasan blocks it off the front foot.

Axar Patel comes into the attack now and starts off with a ripper of a delivery. This is drifted in from around off and on a length, Mushfiqur Rahim looks to press forward and blocks but the ball turns sharply and bounces a bit extra as well, zipping past the outside edge.
Tossed up around off, Mushfiqur Rahim brings out the broom and sweeps it against the turn in front of mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
On off stump, solidly defended off the front foot.
Flatter one around off, Rahim nudges it out on the off side.
Around middle, Mushfiqur Rahim tentatively blocks it out on the leg side.

A repeat of the first delivery as Mushfiqur Rahim is beaten all ends up past the outside edge. Nicely flighted and drifting in from outside off. Rahim looks to block but yet again the ball grips and turns past the outside edge.
On a length with some extra bounce, on off. Hasan fends it to point.
Good length angling it on leg, Hasan defends it to mid on.
FOUR! Well played. Shorter and on off, Hasan hangs back and plays an upper cut over short third man for a boundary!
On a length and outside off shaping it away, Hasan looks to defend it but misses.
Fuller and onto the stumps, Hasan defends it solidly towards mid on.
Bowls it outside off shaping it away, Hasan looks to drive it but misses.

OUT! LBW! Touch fuller and on middle and leg and comes on with the arm. Mushfiqur Rahim looks to block it but gets beaten on the inside edge and gets a rap on his pads. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Mushfiqur Rahim decides to go upstairs. Fair delivery and Ultra Edge shows a flat line. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Mushfiqur Rahim departs. Huge trouble for Bangladesh now as they still trail by 17 runs.
Howout: lbw b Axar Patel

Commentary: Flatter and outside off turning it in, Litton das makes a tight leave. That was close!
Fuller and on off, Litton das taps it to the man at short covers.
Bowls it outside off, Litton das leaves it alone.
This one lands on off, Litton das eases it to the point region.
Fuller and on off, Litton das lunges and defends it out.
On a length and outside off, Hasan shoulders arms at it.
Good length with some extra bounce, Hasan looks to cut it but misses.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Hasan defends it solidly towards mid off.
Another fuller one on middle, Hasan awkwardly flicks it to mid-wicket for a single. Good bowling here from Unadkat!
Fuller one angling it in, Litton Das defends it to mid on.
Fuller and on off, Litton blocks it back towards the bowler. That will be LUNCH on Day 3.
Bowls it full and outside off, Hasan looks to defend it but gets an outside edge as the ball rolls towards backward square leg. They collect two.
This one lands outside off with some turn, Hasan looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Bowls it outside leg, Hasan leaves it alone. Dot.
Slightly shorter one, Hasan knocks it to long on for a single.
Fuller and on off, Litton das defends it off the front foot.
Fuller and on off, Litton Das sweeps it but gets a top edge. The ball carries towards backward square leg and lands safely. The batters collect two.
On a length and on off, Hasan taps it to covers for one.
Fuller and on off, Litton Das blocks it to mid on.
Fuller and on off, Litton Das knocks it to long off. The fielder chases it well. The batters collect three runs.
Good length angling it into the batter, Hasan defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
Another length ball outside off shaping it away a bit, Hasan looks to defend it but misses.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Hasan eases it to mid on and scampers through for a single.
Fuller and on middle, Hasan blocks it back towards the bowler.
Flatter and on off, Hasan works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Litton Das lunges and defends it away.
Slightly shorter and down leg, Litton Das flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Bowls it outside off turning it away, Hasan looks to flick it but misses and the keeper fails to grab it as well. The batters cross for a bye.
Bowls it outside off, Litton Das blocks it out solidly.
On a length and outside off, slower too. Hasan looks to slap it but misses.
On a length with some extra bounce, outside off. Hasan looks to punch it but misses.

On a length and on leg, it nips in a bit further. Hasan looks to block it but misses and gets a rap on his pads. A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. KL Rahul goes upstairs. The replay shows that there was an inside edge and the onfield decision stands NOT OUT! India are now out of reviews now.
Play and a miss. This one lands outside off, Hasan looks to play at it but misses.
Good length and on off, Hasan taps it to covers. Dot.
On a length and on leg, Hasan defends it away.
Bowls it outside off, Litton Das guides it to covers for a single.
Touch fuller and on off, Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Goes fuller this time, on off. Hasan knocks it to mid on for one.
Flatter and on leg, Litton Das flicks it to backward square leg for one. Scores are level now!
Fuller one angling it in, Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Hasan flicks it to backward square leg for one. Bangladesh takes the lead. They lead by 1 run now with 6 wickets in hand.
On a length angling it in, some extra bounce as well. Hasan fends it to mid on.
This one lands outside off, Hasan leaves it alone.
Bowls it outside off swinging it in, Hasan reads it well and leaves it alone.
On a length and outside off, Hasan steers it to point for a single.
Slightly shorter, on off. Litton Das steers it to the man at point.
Good length and on off, Litton Das taps it to the man at covers. Ends with a dot.
Slightly shorter and on off, Hasan steers it straight to the man at covers.
Fuller and on off, Hasan flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
This one lands outside off, Hasan leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Hasan lunges and defends it away.
Fuller one again, Hasan knocks it to the man at mid off.
Flatter and on middle and leg, Hasan flicks it to square leg for a single.
Umesh Yadav comes back into the attack and starts off with a fullish delivery on off, Zakir Hasan strokes it toward extra cover.

FIFTY for Zakir Hasan and he's gone from strength to strength here. Pitched up around middle, Zakir punches it back past the bowler. The fielder from mid on chases it down and they push hard for the third, getting it with ease in the end. Bangladesh will be hoping that Zakir keeps on going.
This is pitched up on off, Litton Das pushes it out on the off side.
Full and around off, Litton Das drives it on the up and square of the wicket through covers for three more runs.
Excellent running! Back of a length and around off, bunted out in front of point for a quick single.

A desperate effort in the deep and Mohammed Siraj saves a run for his side. Full and on the pads, Litton Das clips it through mid-wicket. Siraj runs around from deep backward square leg and dives to his left to keep the ball in play. They take three.
This is angled into middle, Das stays back and defends it out.
Fullish length around off and turning away, this is solidly blocked off the front foot.
Goes even fuller now and tries to slide it in from around off, Litton Das pushes at it and gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A tad shorter and coming on with the arm into the pads. Litton Das goes on the back foot and nudges it down past short leg for a run.
Floated up, on a length and around off, kept out by Zakir Hasan.
Tosses it up now around middle, Zakir presses forward to make the block.
Umesh Yadav hasn't quite found his rhythm yet in this spell. This is a bit shorter and outside off, Litton Das runs it down to third man for an easy single.
Comes from around the wicket to the left-hander and angles in a shortish ball down leg. Zakir Hasan looks to pull but misses.
Good length around off, this is eased away towards point.

OUT! TAKEN! Not the best of deliveries from Umesh Yadav but he has got the big fish. This is short and wide, there to be hit. Zakir Hasan goes after it and slaps it away over backward point. The ball goes off the outer half of the bat and doesn't go the distance. Mohammed Siraj from third man comes in and takes a good low catch to his left. Zakir departs after a fighting knock but he will be disappointed with that shot. Bangladesh lead by 15 runs.
Howout: c Mohammed Siraj b Umesh Yadav

Commentary: Well bowled! Umesh Yadav goes a bit wider of the crease and angles it in on a length and into the off pole. The ball keeps a shade low but Mehidy Hasan manages to fend it away.
Uppish but safe! Goes full now and attacks the pads, Mehidy Hasan looks to flick but ends up chipping it wide of the man at silly mid on.
Floats it up on off stump, Litton Das pushes it toward cover.

FOUR! Streaky but a bit intentional as well. Tosses it up wide of the off stump, Litton Das presses forward and looks to open the face of the bat and guide it square of the wicket. The ball goes off the outside edge and flies past the diving fielder at first slip into the third man fence.
Drifted onto middle, Das keeps it out.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Virat Kohli anticipates early and ends up going the wrong way. Axar Patel holds it back a touch and bowls it around off stump. Litton Das looks to drive with the turn but gets an outside edge. Kohli moves to his right but the ball goes to his left and he is unable to adjust in time. The ball hits the hand and trickles away into the third man fence.
Nicely tossed up outside off, Litton Das looks to thrash it over extra cover but mistimes it toward sweeper cover for one.
Pushed through a bit and angling into the stumps, Mehidy Hasan blocks it out.
Around the top of off, Litton Das blocks it from inside his crease.
Just a touch fuller and angled into middle and off, the ball keeps a bit low and Das blocks it out.
On a hard length and around off, tapped away toward cover.
Back of a length around the fifth stump line, Litton Das defends it off the back foot.
Full and around off, driven straight to the man at extra cover.
This is banged in short and outside off, Das dabs it down toward backward point and gets across for a single.
A bit shorter and on the pads, Litton Das goes back in his crease and pushes it out in front of mid-wicket for a run.
Angles this one in on middle and bowls it full, Mehidy Hasan blocks it out.

OUT! LBW! Mehidy Hasan departs and Bangladesh are now six down with a narrow lead of 26 runs. Axar Patel angles it in on a length and from a bit wider of the crease as well. This one pitches around the off stump and Mehidy looks to sweep with the angle as there is no one patrolling the square boundary on the leg side. Mehidy misses and gets pinged in front. The Indian players appeal and the finger goes up. Mehidy has a long chat with his partner before he accepts his fate and starts walking. Bangladesh in troubled waters now.
Howout: lbw b Axar Patel

Commentary: This is fired in around the off pole and Nurul Hasan manages to keep it out.
JAFFA! Fuller and around off, just slows it up a touch. Nurul Hasan looks to block but the ball turns away sharply just going past the outside edge.
Drops it a bit short and bowls it on the pads, Nurul Hasan works it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Yadav gets in the yorker now around off stump, Litton Das digs it out towards cover-point.
Length ball angling in from middle and Das tucks it away past square leg for a single.
FOUR! A tad shorter and outside off, Nurul Hasan accepts the width and slaps it away in front of cover-point for a boundary.
Fullish length, angling into the pads, Nurul Hasan manages to keep it out.

That could have gone anywhere. A bumper now, angled into the helmet of the batter. Nurul Hasan tries to get inside the line and take it on but mistimes it over the square leg region. The batters come back for two.

Nicely played! Back of a length and outside off, Nurul Hasan punches it off the back foot in between point and cover. The two fielders chase it down and manage to stop the boundary. Enough time for the batters to take three there.
Nagging length, close to the off pole and staying low. Nurul Hasan manages to keep it out.
Quicker one, on a length and angling in from around off. Axar Patel gets a bit of extra bounce but Nurul Hasan manages to keep it down in front of short leg.
Sliding onto the pads, this is worked away 'round the corner for one.
Bowls it on a length and drifts it onto middle, Litton Das presents a dead bat at it.
Prodigious turn that time. Slows it up a touch and floats it around off, Litton Das looks to block off the front foot but the ball turns away square and goes a long way past the outside edge.
Flighted delivery around off, Litton Das lunges forward and makes the block.
SIX! WOW! Ravichandran Ashwin comes back into the attack and starts with a tossed-up delivery on middle. Nurul Hasan dances down the track and whacks it over the long on fence for a biggie.
Pushes this one through a bit quicker and around off, Nurul Hasan edges it down with soft hands toward third man and races back for the second. Good running.
Gives it a lot more air and drifts it onto leg stump, Nurul Hasan defends it out.
Quicker one, around middle, Nurul Hasan tentatively keeps it out.
Drops it short now and outside off, Nurul Hasan goes deep in his crease to cut it in front of the man at deep point for a couple of runs.
Two more and the lead goes past 50 now! Short again and around off, this is chopped away and past the cover fielder for a couple of runs. This is good counter-attacking batting from Nurul Hasan.
FOUR! Litton Das gets into the act now. Tossed up on off stump, Das gets a big stride forward and sweeps it firmly into the mid-wicket fence.
This is sliding into leg stump, Litton Das blocks it out.

FOUR! Bangladesh are on a roll here and the Indian spinners for the first time in this innings are under a bit of pressure. Tossed up around off, Litton Das gets down on one knee and brooms it in front of the square on the leg side for another boundary.
Flatter delivery around off, Das taps it towards point.
Nagging length around off, Litton Das goes on the back foot and ease it toward cover.
This one almost goes through! Quicker one on a nagging length and on off stump. Litton Das goes on the back foot instead of coming forward but just about manages to get an inside edge on it.
Tossed up just outside off, Hasan guides it to backward point for a single.
Bowls it on the leg side, Das works it to square leg for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Hasan steers it to point for one again.
Leg bye! This is shorter and down leg, Litton Das looks to flick off the back foot but gets it off his pads toward short fine leg. They get a leg bye.
Short and wide outside off, Nurul Hasan cuts it to point for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Litton Das punches it to point for a brace.
On a length and around off, a bit of turn and bounce on offer as well. Nurul Hasan manages to defend it out.
Pre-meditated from Nurul Hasan, looks to shuffle across and scoop but misses the shorter ball over the stumps.

FOUR! It seems to be a dropped catch but maybe, there wasn't any bat involved. Tossed up on a length and Axar Patel extracts sharp turn and bounce yet again. Nurul Hasan looks to block off the front foot but the ball gets a feather off the outside edge and flicks the keeper's gloves before going past Virat Kohli at first slip and into the fence.
Flatter one on middle, nudged away onto the leg side.
At the stumps and blocked away.

Is that a fair catch? Virat Kohli isn't sure but seems to have got his man. The umpires come together and go upstairs. The soft signal is Not Out. This is tossed up around off stump and there's some sharp turn on offer as well. Nurul Hasan looks to press forward but gets an outside edge toward first slip. The replays show that the ball just bounced before going into Kohli's hands. Nurul is a relieved man.
Slightly shorter and on off, Das eases it to short mid-wicket. They wanted a single but decided not to take it.
Tosses it on off, Das defends it to the point region.
Another one on off, Das taps it to the man at covers.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Das flicks it to mid-wicket for one.

Fuller and on off, Hasan looks to defend it but gets gets inbetween the bat and pads. Ashwin thinks it was pad first and appeals but the umpire is unmoved. India are also out of reviews so the onfield decision stands!
This is on off as Hasan defends it to the cover region.
Fuller and on middle, Das nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller and on off, Hasan plays it towards the man at mid off. It carries for a while but lands safely.

OUT! STUMPED! This is slightly shorter and on off turning it away, Nurul Hasan shimmies down the wicket to loft it but misses it completely. Rishabh Pant pouches it and whips off the bails in no time. Bangladesh lost their seventh and they are in huge trouble now! The lead currently stands at 72 runs.
Howout: st Rishabh Pant b Axar Patel

Commentary: Quicker and outside off, Taskin Ahmed looks to play at it but misses.
Fuller and on off, Taskin Ahmed defends it with soft hands towards mid off.
Another one on middle, turning it away, Taskin Ahmed looks to defend it but gets a rap on his pads. A loud appeal but the finger stays down and India is out of reviews. They are getting closer!
Fuller and on off, Litton Das lunges and defends it away.
Bowls it fuller again, Litton Das flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Tosses it on off, Litton Das knocks it to mid on for one.
Bowls it on leg, Ahmed works it to mid-wicket for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Das defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller one and on leg, Das works it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller one and on leg, Das flicks it to deep backward square leg for a brace. Good running!
Bowls it on middle as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Das opens the face of the bat and plays it uppishly towards covers for one.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Ahmed gets on his knee and slog sweeps it over mid-wicket for a boundary!
Fuller one again, Ahmed taps it to short covers and calls for one but is sent back.
This one lands on off, Ahmed defends it with soft hands towards mid on.
Fuller and on off, Das flicks it to square leg for a single.

Three runs and it will be leg byes as well. On a length and drifting down leg, Taskin Ahmed looks to work it fine but misses. The ball goes off the pads and trickles down to fine leg before it is cut off.
Tossed up on middle and leg, flicked away toward mid-wicket.
Around middle, Litton Das watchfully blocks it out.
Floated up full and on off stump, Litton Das sweeps it toward deep backward square leg for a single.
Looks for the carrom ball but spills it down leg for the keeper to collect.
Flatter and quicker and around off, this is chopped off the back foot and in front of point.

What a review! Litton Das survives and there's a huge cheer from the crowd. Axar Patel fires this one in on the pads. Das looks to work it leg side but the ball skids on and thuds into the pads. There is a huge appeal and Litton Das has been adjudged lbw. Das does review it but this could be a huge moment in the game. Nothing on UltraEdge but Ball Tracking shows that the ball is going on with the arm and missing leg stump.
Around off, kept out by Litton Das.
Shorter and on the pads, this is worked off the back foot through mid-wicket for a single.
Comes from over the wicket now and bowls it a bit shorter around the pads, Taskin Ahmed fails to work it away.
Flighted delivery, drifted on the pads and Taskin Ahmed gets an inside edge that goes wide of the fielder stationed at leg slip.

DROPPED! That will be FIFTY for Litton Das and this has been a very important knock for his side. Ravichandran Ashwin bowls a lovely delivery, drifting into off and turning away sharply off the deck. Das gets squared up and the outside edge is found. Virat Kohli at first slip springs to his right but fails to grab it with his right hand. The ball goes towards third man and a single is taken.
A tad shorter and down leg, this is pulled away toward fine leg for a couple of runs.
Just short! Flighted delivery around middle, Taskin Ahmed looks to block off the front foot but gets a faint inside edge that falls in front of the man at leg slip.
Tosses it up now, full and around off, Taskin Ahmed mistimes the heave through mid on and picks up a single.
FOUR! Up and over! Another one that's tossed up, Litton Das shimmies down the track and lofts it over mid on for a boundary.

Flatter delivery around off, Litton Das goes on the back foot and plays it late toward third man. The man from first slip chases it down and the batters get a couple of runs. The lead is now inching closer to 100 runs.
FOUR! Broomed away and the lead is now worth 102 runs! Tossed up on middle and leg, Taskin Ahmed slog-sweeps it between the man at deep mid-wicket and deep square leg for a boundary.
On the pads and this is swept away fine toward deep backward square leg for a couple of runs. This has been a good fightback thus far from Bangladesh.
Good running. Slower and shorter around off, Taskin Ahmed nudges it toward backward point and scampers through for one.
Shorter and around off, this is punched away off the back foot toward cover for a single.

Slightly shorter and down leg, Taskin Ahmed looks to pull off the back foot but mistimes it past the man at leg slip for a single. The ball seems to have comes off the thigh pad and is signalled as leg byes.
Drifted onto the pads, flicked away through mid-wicket for one. That will be TEA on Day 3!

Starts off with a good-length delivery around off. This one jags back in a long way and Litton Das gets squared up while looking to flick. The ball hits him high on the pads and there's half an appeal for lbw but it is turned down.
FOUR! Litton Das isn't going to back down here. Pitched up outside off, Das lofts it up and over the point region for a boundary.
Litton Das looks to charge down the track but Siraj pulls the length back a bit. Das ends up slicing it safely over covers for a single. The 200 is now up for Bangladesh.
A length ball, angling across from leg stump, Taskin Ahmed nudges it toward short mid-wicket.
Beaten! A touch fuller and slanted just across the off stump. Taskin Ahmed looks to play at it but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Banged in short and outside off, Taskin Ahmed looks to take it on but is beaten all ends up.
Shorter delivery on middle, this is worked away to deep mid-wicket for an easy single.
Short again and down the leg side, Taskin Ahmed gets down on one knee and pulls it toward fine leg for a run.
Quicker one, sliding through on off stump. Litton Das defends it off the back foot.
Nagging length outside off and turning away. Litton Das gets caught on the crease and tentatively looks to cut but is beaten past the outside edge.
FOUR! Poor delivery from Axar Patel, a fraction shorter and outside off, Litton Das cuts it past the fielder at backward point and picks up another boundary.

A slight mix-up in the middle but no harm is done. Quicker and shorter around off, this is tapped away off the back foot to the right of the man at point. Taskin Ahmed looks to get to the striker's end but is sent back halfway down the track by Litton Das and rightly so.

FOUR! Back of a length, at 143 clicks and angling across the off stump. Taskin Ahmed stands tall and guides it off the outer half of the bat past the slip cordon and into the fence. The 50-run stand is up between these two.
Goes fuller now at 140 clicks and tightens the line around off stump. Taskin looks to play at it but the ball keeps low and beats the outside edge.
Excellent running! Good length around the pads, Taskin Ahmed dabs it down in front of mid-wicket and sets off for the quick single.
On a hard length, angling into middle and leg, Das manages to play it on the leg side and pick up a single.
Full and down the leg side, Ahmed looks to flick but misses.
A bumper now, over leg stump and bowled at a good pace as well. Taskin Ahmed ducks under it well though.
This is fired in around off stump, Litton Das presses forward and nudges it onto the leg side for a single.
This is tossed up around off stump, Taskin Ahmed defends it off the front foot.
A tad shorter and turning it into the pads, Taskin flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery around off, blocked out.
Looks to fire it in from around off, Taskin prods forward to defend.
This is angled into the stumps, Taskin works it toward short mid-wicket.
Bowls it full and wide, Litton Das looks to drive it straight but mistimes it back to the bowler who threatens to throw the ball back onto the stumps.
Hits a good length and angles it in from around off. The scrambled seam makes the ball bounce a bit extra and Litton Das manages to keep it down in front of the man at gully.
Fuller, at 141 clicks and angled into middle. Litton Das looks to loft it over mid on but mistimes it badly.
Goes a bit wider of the crease and angles it in on a hard length. Litton Das stays back and dabs it past point for a single.

Litton Das knew straightaway that it was pitching outside leg. A length ball around leg and angling across. Taskin Ahmed looks to flick but falls over a bit and gets pinged in front of the stumps. There is a huge appeal for lbw from Mohammed Siraj, pleading for it and the finger does go up. Taskin Ahmed has immediately reviewed it and if the ball is pitching outside leg, he might be saved. Nothing on UltraEdge and Ball Tracking does show that it is pitching well outside the line of leg stump and the decision is reversed.
Short of a length and outside off, Taskin Ahmed throws his hands at it and slashes it wide of the man at third man for a couple of runs.
Flatter and on middle as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Another one on middle, Das defends it to the gully region.
Bowls it on off this time, Das steers it to point for a single.
Fuller one and on off, it keeps a tad low. Ahmed plays it with soft hands towards covers for a single.
This one lands on off, Das lunges and defends it away.
Fuller and on off, Das guides it to covers for a single.

OUT! TIMBER! Mohammed Siraj, you beauty! Keeps on making use of that scrambled seam and bowls it on a good length around off. This one jags back in sharply off the deck. Litton Das looks to defend it but gets caught on the crease and is beaten on the inside edge as the ball rattles into the stumps. An excellent innings from Litton Das comes to an end as he walks back into the hut for 73! Bangladesh lead by 132 runs.
Howout: b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: On a length and outside off, Taijul gets in two minds but leaves it alone in the end.
Fuller and just outside off, Taijul looks to defend it but misses. Close!
Another one outside off shaping it away, Taijul looks to play at it but misses again!
Fuller and on leg, Taijul clips it to backward square leg for a single.
Touch fuller and on off, Ahmed defends it solidly towards covers.

OUT! LBW! This one is a touch fuller and angling in from middle and leg, Taijul Islam looks to block it but misses and gets a rap on his pads. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Taijul Islam decides to go upstairs immediately. Fair delivery and Ultra Edge shows no spike. Ball Tracking shows three reds as the ball is just clipping leg stump and Bangladesh go nine down in a jiffy!
Howout: lbw b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: Fuller and outside off, Ahmed looks to play at it but misses.
Bowls it down leg, Ahmed looks to defend it but misses and gets his pads. A stifled appeal turned down.
FOUR! Fuller and down leg, Khaled Ahmed reads it well and gives it a slight tickle as the ball races away the fine leg fence for a boundary!
Fuller on the stumps, Khaled defends it back to the bowler.
Turn and bounce here, Khaled gets an edge through to the third man, but decides not to take a single.
Back of a length angling in, Taskin looks to go for a big heave but misses.
Fuller and on off, Taskin Ahmed taps it to the man at mid off.
FOUR! Smashed away. Slightly shorter and on off, Taskin Ahmed hangs back and smashes it over mid off for a boundary!
On a length and on leg, Taskin Ahmed awkwardly lifts it towards square for a single. The ball carried a bit but landed safely.
Touch fuller and just outside off, Khaled Ahmed looks to play at it but misses.
Fuller and on off, Khaled Ahmed defends it solidly towards the man at covers.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Taskin Ahmed flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a brace. This is good running between the wickets.
Fuller and on off, Taskin Ahmed defends it to mid off.
Another fuller one as this is again defended towards the man at mid off.
Fuller and keeps it a tad low, Taskin Ahmed eases it to short covers.
Another fuller one as this one is defended back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, Taskin Ahmed knocks it but finds the man at mid off.
Fuller and on off, Khaled Ahmed lunges and blocks it away.

OUT! RUN OUT! This was a blunder from the Bangladesh batters and they are bowled out for 231. Bowls it on off, Khaled Ahmed pushes it to short mid-wicket and sets off for a single. Shubman Gill grabs it quickly and throws it a bit high towards Axar Patel at the non striker's end. He is quick enough to whip the bails off. The replay shows that Khaled Ahmed was just behind the line and Bangladesh are bundled out for 231 runs. Bangladesh end with a lead of 144 runs.
Howout: run out (Shubman Gill / Axar Patel)

Commentary: Shakib Al Hasan starts right on the money and almost gets a wicket off the very first delivery! Fuller and on middle and leg, Shubman Gill looks to block it but misses and gets a rap on his pads. A loud appeal turned and Shakib Al Hasan straightaway goes for a review. Ball Tracking shows that it was just missing leg and the onfield decision stands NOT OUT and Bangladesh lose a review as well! Shubman Gill breathes a sigh of relief.
Fuller and on off, Shubman Gill defends it solidly to mid off.
This one lands outside off, Shubman Gill lunges and blocks it away.
Bowls it on off, Shubman Gill lunges and defends it to the man at mid off.
Another fuller one and on off, Shubman Gill flicks it to square leg for one. He gets off the mark!

Did that go to hand? Slightly shorter and on leg, KL Rahul tucks it to the right of the man at short leg and Mominul Haque fails to react quickly. Rahul picks up a single and it is a big opportunity missed for Bangladesh.
Fuller on the stumps, Rahul defends it back to the bowler.
Turn and bounce that beats the outside edge and goes through to the keeper.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended towards short covers.
Turns it in from outside off, KL Rahul eases it to mid off.
Fuller and on middle, KL Rahul tucks it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller again, on off. Shubman Gill defends it solidly.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Nicely tossed and on off turning it away, drawing the batter forward. KL Rahul looks to block it off the front foot but gets beaten and gets an outside edge. Nurul Hasan behind the sticks is quick to react to it and takes a sharp catch to his right. Shakib Al Hasan is delighted as India lose their skipper for another low score. Bangladesh have an early and a much needed breakthrough in the chase!
Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to square leg for one.
Tosses it up here, Gill uses his feet and defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Shubman Gill defends it solidly.
Another fuller one giving it some air, Shubman Gill uses his feet and blocks it away.
Bowls it on off, Shubman Gill defends it to the man at mid off.
Bowls it on middle and leg, Cheteshwar Pujara lunges and blocks it away.
Another fuller one and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it forward.
Another one on off, Cheteshwar Pujara covers his line and blocks it away.
This one lands down leg, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to block it but gets a rap on his pads. Dot.
Flatter and on the pads as Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back towards the bowler.
This was similar to the last delivery, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back towards the bowler again.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Shubman Gill flicks it but finds the man at short mid-wicket.
Another one down leg, Shubman Gill looks to flick it but gets a rap on his pads. A stifled appeal turned down.
Fuller and on off, Shubman Gill moves forward and defends it to mid off and scampers through for a single.
Fuller again outside off turning it away, Cheteshwar Pujara moves forward and blocks it with his pads.
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! This one lands down leg, Cheteshwar Pujara sweeps it through fine leg for a boundary!
Nicely drifted onto middle and leg, Shubman Gill keeps it out off the front foot.
Gives it a bit more air and floats it around off, Gill pushes it out on the off side.
Fuller and on off stump, Gill defends it out off the front foot.
And again! Tossed up on off stump, Gill lunges forward to defend.
Flights it up now around middle but Gill stays solid in defense.
Maiden! This is pushed through on off stump, Shubman Gill blocks it out.
A tad shorter and slower around off, Cheteshwar Pujara has enough time to rock back and punch it through cover for a run.
Nagging length, floated up around off, Shubman Gill goes on the back foot to keep it out.
Shubman Gill steps out and looks to use his feet but Shakib fires it in at the toes. Gill ends up pushing it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery around middle and leg, tucked away to mid-wicket.
Floats it up now around middle, Gill defends it out.

A bit of a misfield and they get two. On a length and around middle, this is pushed away toward mid on for a quick single. Mushfiqur Rahim comes rushing in and overruns the ball and the batters get an additional run.

OUT! STUMPED! Nurul Hasan with a brilliant recovery and all of a sudden, India are two down. Mehidy Hasan comes into the attack and gets a wicket off his very first delivery. Tosses it up on a shorter length and well outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara comes down the track but gets beaten in the flight. Pujara tries to adjust but gets an inside edge off the pads. Nurul Hasan just about manages to collect the ball and dislodges the bails. The third umpire checks it and finds that Pujara failed to get his bat down in time and has to walk back.
Howout: st Nurul Hasan b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: This is fired in on off stump, Axar Patel keeps it out.
Almost skids through. Nagging length, around off and sliding in. Axar Patel looks to block off the front foot but gets a faint inside edge onto the pads.
Around off again and kept out by Axar Patel.
This one is angling into the pads, Axar Patel looks to block but gets it off the inside edge towards square leg.

A huge appeal for lbw and the bowler and keeper seem certain about it. The umpire remains unmoved and Shakib Al Hasan doesn't review it either. This is pushed through quicker and into off stump. Axar Patel strides out to defend but gets a faint inside edge onto the pads.
Tossed up around middle, Shubman Gill keeps it out.

Close again and Shubman Gill looks nevry out there. Shakib Al Hasan angles this one in on a nagging length and into the pads. Gill gets pushed onto the back foot and the ball keeps low as well. The ball hits the pads and seems to be going down leg as there is a stifled appeal from Bangladesh.
Drops it a bit short and around off, Shubman Gill steers it off the back foot and through point for a single.
This is flighted down leg, Axar Patel gets a fine tickle on it. The ball runs away towards the fine leg fence but Mehidy Hasan chases it down and saves a run for his side.
Tossed up around off, Shubman Gill uses his feet well and pushes it down to long off for a single.
Flatter delivery on the pads, Axar Patel stays back and defends it on the leg side.
Big turn! Tossed up on a shorter length and around off. Shubman Gill comes down the track to block but gets undone by the turn and hit on the pads.
Turning in from around middle and Gill blocks it onto the leg side.
Fuller now and at the stumps, Shubman Gill knocks it down to long on for a single.
Turn and bounce! Comes from around the wicket and bowls it on a length around off, the ball turns away square leaving Axar Patel completely bamboozled.
Flighted delivery, Axar Patel uses his feet and drives it back past the bowler for a run.
Nicely tossed up around middle, Shubman Gill watchfully defends it out.
Quicker one, on a nagging length and around middle, Axar Patel goes deep in his crease to defend it out.
FOUR! Just a fraction shorter and Axar Patel pounces on it. This is bowled around off, Patel rocks back and punches it through covers for a boundary.
This is tossed up on off stump and Axar Patel defends it out.
This is drifted onto middle and leg, Patel presses forward to defend.
Floated, full and at the toes, Axar Patel works it 'round the corner for one.
Tosses it up full and around leg stump, Shubman Gill comes down the pitch and pushes it to silly mid on.
This is shorter and around off, Axar Patel backs away and plays it to short extra cover.
Tossed up full on off stump, Axar Patel defends it off the front foot.
Looks to fire this one into middle and leg, Patel stays solid in defense.
Drops it shorter on off and looks to turn it away, Axar Patel mistimes it off the back foot onto the leg side.
This is speared into middle and leg, Axar Patel gets hurried but manages to keep it out.
On off stump, this is driven down to long off for a single.
Starts off a bit of a loosener. This is a fraction shorter and outside off, Axar Patel slaps it away wide of the man at the backward point fence and collects a couple of runs.
Good length, angling across the left-hander and it is left alone for the keeper to correct.
Hits the length hard and bowls it around off, Axar Patel hops and keeps it out towards mid off.
Short again and around off, this is nicely punched away well in front of the square on the off side for a couple of runs.
Goes a bit fuller and angles it across the off stump, Axar Patel shoulders arms at it.
Comes from around the wicket now and serves it on a length around off at 140 clicks. Axar Patel plays it toward point.
This is floated up outside off, Shubman Gill blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! STUMPED! Mehidy Hasan completely outfoxes Shubman Gill who walks back after a nervy inning. This is nicely flighted on a length and outside off. Gill looks to step out and get to the pitch of the ball but is beaten in the flight. Also, the ball doesn't turn in rather drifts away beating the outside edge. Nurul Hasan whips off the bails in a flash and Gill is well out of his crease. Mehidy Hasan gets his second wicket and India in a spot of bother here. 116 runs still needed with 7 wickets in hand.
Howout: st Nurul Hasan b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: A tad shorter and turning in from around middle. Virat Kohli goes deep in his crease and flicks it right of the man at mid-wicket who makes a half-stop. Kohli denies the single on the misfield and rightly so.
Tossed up on off stump, Kohli keeps it out.
This is floated up on middle, Kohli reaches forward to defend.
Mehidy Hasan pulls back the length and bowls it around off, Virat Kohli goes on the back foot to keep it out. A wicket-maiden then for Mehidy.
Taijul Islam comes back into the attack and starts off with a fuller one on the pads, Axar Patel flicks it straight to square leg.
Nagging length on off stump, Axar Patel tentatively blocks it out.
Tossed up around leg stump, Axar Patel plays it with soft hands and towards mid-wicket.
Taijul Islam switches to over the wicket and drifts it onto the pads. Axar Patel tickles it through short fine leg and picks up a couple of runs.
Tossed up on off stump, turning in, Axar Patel defends it down the pitch.

Holds it back a touch and pulls the length back as well. The ball is delivered around off stump, it turns in and bounces a bit extra as well. Axar Patel gets taken by surprise but manages to keep it out.
Fuller and outside off, Kohli looks to defend it but misses.
Another fuller and on off, Kohli blocks it to short leg.
This one lands on off, Kohli eases it to the man at short covers.
Fuller and on off, Kohli knocks it to mid on for one.
Shorter and outside off turning it away, Patel leaves it alone.
Turns it in from outside off, Patel defend it solidly off the front foot.
Fuller and on off, Kohli defends it solidly off the front foot.
Fuller one this time, Kohli defends it away. Half an appeal as the pad was in front of the bat but the replays show that the ball did hit the bat.
Quicker one here, Kohli defends watchfully.
Bowls it on off, Kohli defends it solidly off the front foot.
Fuller and on off, Kohli taps it to the man at covers.

Virat Kohli knew it hit the blade and lives to fight another day. This is flighted on a length and drifted in from around off stump. Kohli presses forward to defend but seems to have missed it as the ball raps him on the pads. Taijul Islam appeals loudly and after a long thought, the umpire raises the finger. It is reviewed instantaneously and UltraEdge shows that there was a faint inside edge on it.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Axar Patel lunges and blocks it away.
Another fuller one as this is defended towards the man at mid off.
Fuller on the stumps, Axar defends it to the short cover region.
Bowls it on middle turning it in, Axar Patel eases it back towards the bowler.
Fuller on the stumps, Axar pushes it to the short cover fielder.
Bowls it outside off, Axar Patel blocks it to mid off. A maiden from Mehidy Hasan!
Fuller and on off, Virat Kohli eases it to the man at short covers.
Another fuller one, Virat Kohli taps it to the man at point.
Bowls it on off, Virat Kohli defends it to mid on.
